<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2000-09-01</DATELINE><TITLE>Viral mechanisms of immune evasion</TITLE><BODY>Abstract During the millions of years they have coexisted with their hosts, viruses have learned how to manipulate host immune control mechanisms. Viral gene functions provide an overview of many relevant principles in cell biology and immunology. Our knowledge of viral gene functions must be integrated into virusâ€“host interaction networks to understand viral pathogenesis, and could lead to new anti-viral strategies and the ability to exploit viral functions as tools in medicine.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>